<main class="l-styleguide">
  <h1 class="l-styleguide__title">Styleguide</h1>

  <p class="standfirst">Going to university is all about having a good time, discovering yourself and making new friends, right? Well, yes, but hopefully you'll learn a lot and get a good qualification as well.</p>

  <p>However, if you really want to have a great three years it’s important to budget, because after paying rent you’ll probably end up spending around £600 a month. Here are some tips to help you get the most out of your time away.</p>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Tags</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/tags' %> 
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Article Info</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/article_info' %>
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Inline callout</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/inline_callout' %>
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Collapsible</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/collapsible' %>
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/next_steps' %>
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Article Tiles</h2>
    <%= render 'shared/article_tile' %>
  </section>

  <section class="l-styleguide-section">
    <h2>Social sharing buttons</h2>
    <p>Buttons placed at the top or the bottom of an article on the blog so that a user can share that article. To ensure the buttons are accessible for screen reader users the code must be placed after the article but can be placed visually anywhere on the page.</p>
    <p>When the viewport exceeds 720px the buttons with fix to the right side of the screen</p>
    <%= render 'shared/sharing_buttons' %>
  </section>
</main>
